    "created_at": "2026-02-24T17:24:40Z",
    "raw_text": "Another extra benefit: once major upstream projects ship stable ABI wheels (e.g. numpy and scipy), it will be easier for downstream projects (e.g. scikit-learn) to run their own tests against the `main` branch of CPython (or a specific PR branch) without having to rebuild those upstream dependencies from source (which can be computationally or operationally expensive).",
