    "created_at": "2026-02-26T17:37:49Z",
    "raw_text": "I was asked for a comment/quote, so here it is. Please feel free to use or not use as you see fit, or tweak a bit. And thanks again Petr, Steve, Nathan, and whoever else is helping out for all the energy poured into this topic.\r\n\r\n\"SciPy and a number of other projects in the scientific Python ecosystem are quite interested in starting to use the Stable ABI, in particular to reduce the maintenance load of [providing more wheels](https://pypackaging-native.github.io/meta-topics/user_expectations_wheels/). With recent CPython, Cython and NumPy releases, this now seems possible. The performance costs seem acceptable and small, although we'll only really build confidence in that assessment after having made the switch.\"",
